			<p>After working for twenty-five years as a professional gardener, <span class="smallcaps"><strong>Charles Goodrich</strong></span> has worn out his knees, so he&rsquo;s retooling to become a fifth-grade teacher. He lives in Corvallis, Oregon, and has written two poetry chapbooks: <em>Insects of South Corvallis</em> (Knot House) and <em>New Pests Every Day</em>.</p><a href="/contributors/charles-goodrich" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
